Day 2 Blue Team Workflow (Database Service)
Operational Checklist + Commands

🟦 1. Verify Redis + LAMP Configs Before Touching Anything
Purpose: confirm nothing drifted overnight and check for Red Team tampering.
Commands
# redis configs
sudo cat /etc/redis/redis.conf | less
sudo ls -l /etc/redis
sudo ls -l /var/lib/redis
sudo ls -l /var/log/redis

# apache configs
sudo apache2ctl -S
sudo cat /etc/apache2/apache2.conf | less
sudo cat /etc/apache2/conf-available/security.conf | less

# php configs
sudo find /etc/php -name php.ini -exec grep -H "expose_php" {} \;

# mysql configs
sudo cat /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf | less
sudo mysql -e "SELECT User,Host FROM mysql.user;"



🟦 2. Run Your Hardening Scripts (LAMP, Redis, Box Hardening)
Purpose: re‑assert your baseline and undo any overnight changes.
Commands
sudo bash lamp_hardening.sh
sudo bash redis_hardening.sh
sudo bash box_hardening.sh


Notes
- Run Redis script first if you suspect tampering.
- LAMP script second (since Day 2 added a LAMP vuln).
- Box hardening last (firewall, users, perms).

🟦 3. Re‑Check Firewall Rules
Purpose: ensure Red Team didn’t open ports or add IPs.
Commands
sudo ufw status verbose
sudo iptables -L -n -v
sudo ss -tulpn


Expected
- Only ports: 22, 80, 443
- Only allowed IPs: 10.10.10.10, 10.10.10.11

🟦 4. Enumerate Users, Processes, and Services
Purpose: catch persistence, rogue accounts, or malicious processes.
Commands
# users
cat /etc/passwd
sudo awk -F: '($3 == 0) {print}' /etc/passwd   # check for extra root users

# groups
cat /etc/group

# processes
ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head
ps aux | grep -vE "root|redis|mysql|apache" | grep -iE "nc|python|perl|php|bash"

# services
systemctl --type=service --state=running


Look for
- Suspicious usernames
- Python reverse shells
- Netcat listeners
- Cron jobs you didn’t create

🟦 5. Re‑Baseline File Integrity (Directory Hashing Script)
Purpose: create a fresh Day 2 baseline after hardening.
Commands
sudo bash directory_hashing.sh


Typical directories to hash
/etc
/var/www
/redis
/var/lib/redis
/home



🟦 6. Document Everything (Your Notes)
Purpose: track changes for scoring, rollback, and incident response.
Record
- Redis config state
- Apache + PHP config state
- MySQL users + DB list
- Firewall rules
- Suspicious processes killed
- New hashes generated

